<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">These reviews pretty much sum up my experience. I loved the second part, as difficult as it was to read at times. In part 3, I just felt like &quot;massive<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">These reviews pretty much sum up my experience. I loved the second part, as difficult as it was to read at times. In part 3, I just felt like "massive depressing thing" happened to his kids, and then more "massive depressing thing" and then? You guessed it, more "massive depressing thing" so I was expecting the end to somewhat explain a twist as to why the preacher had to die and why Pete did it and why his wife can now get out of the asylum and lead a somewhat happy life! But no, just more "massive depressing thing". Frustrating.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
