        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2518755443" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2979033208476822199">I hated this book. It was racist, sexist, and most damningly - boring. The way Grisham talked about the black characters was condescending and the way he talked about Mary Ann was both racist and sexist. The reasons behind the crime were obvious and boring. If Grisham wanted to write a book about the horrors of the Pacific theater during World War II he should&apos;ve just written that book, but those chapters merely served to point out the lack in substance in the rest of the book. I don&apos;t have symp</span>
  <span id="freeText2979033208476822199" style="display:none">I hated this book. It was racist, sexist, and most damningly - boring. The way Grisham talked about the black characters was condescending and the way he talked about Mary Ann was both racist and sexist. The reasons behind the crime were obvious and boring. If Grisham wanted to write a book about the horrors of the Pacific theater during World War II he should've just written that book, but those chapters merely served to point out the lack in substance in the rest of the book. I don't have sympathy for a family losing their land because their patriarch committed murder and I don't have sympathy for someone who planned a murder and refuses to divulge a motive to help their family understand.<br /><br />I've loved some of Grisham's past work and this was so bad that it makes me suspect that I was wrong to have enjoyed his writing ever!<br /><br />I read an e-ARC through NetGalley.</span>
