<div id="review_2679485764" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2679485764" />
    <a title="Wanda Keith" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/63582728-wanda-keith"><img alt="Wanda Keith" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2679485764?book_show_action=true">Jan 18, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Wanda Keith" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Wanda Keith" href="/user/show/63582728-wanda-keith">Wanda Keith</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2679485764" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15493747828490770821">This is absolutely one of the worst books I have ever read. I am not sure why I continued to read when the entire book seemed to make no sense, other than the fact that John Grisham used to write great fiction and I was waiting for that writer to show up. He never did! There were no redeemable characters in the book and the story went in so many directions that I found myself unable to follow the path. A large chunk of the book was right out of &apos;Ghost Soldiers&apos;, a book about the Bataan Death Mar</span>
  <span id="freeText15493747828490770821" style="display:none">This is absolutely one of the worst books I have ever read. I am not sure why I continued to read when the entire book seemed to make no sense, other than the fact that John Grisham used to write great fiction and I was waiting for that writer to show up. He never did! There were no redeemable characters in the book and the story went in so many directions that I found myself unable to follow the path. A large chunk of the book was right out of 'Ghost Soldiers', a book about the Bataan Death March, and I am still trying to figure out why it was such a big part of this book. I keep saying I am done with Grisham as he seems to think he can throw anything out there and his fans will buy it and maybe this time I will stick to it. Don't waste your time or money on this one.<br />#Amazon</span>
  <a data-text-id="15493747828490770821" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
